parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of airbags to deploy in the event of a crash can lead to serious injuries or fatalities, as the occupants are not provided with the necessary protection.
symptoms: Airbags do not deploy during a collision
resulting in occupants hitting their heads on the steering wheel or other interior components
leading to injuries such as concussions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty catalytic converter can cause overheating of the engine, transmission, and radiator, leading to premature wear and damage to these components, resulting in costly repairs and potentially causing accidents due to loss of vehicle control.
Warped rotors can cause vibrations, uneven brake wear, and reduced braking performance, increasing the risk of accidents.
Faulty brake components can lead to reduced braking performance, increasing the risk of accidents.
